Boil a large #pot{} of @salted water{for boiling} for the @dried rigatoni{180%g}.

When boiling, add the rigatoni to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve 2 tbsp of pasta water (double for 4p) then drain the pasta in a #colander{} and pop back in the pot, off the heat.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{for cooking}.

Once hot, add the @prawns{150%g}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the garlic and @paprika{2%sachets} and fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir through the @peas{120%g} and @Worcester sauce{1%sachet} and allow to warm through.

Add the @creme fraiche{110%g}, @green pesto{1%sachet} and pasta water.

Simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the pasta and mix until everything is coated in sauce and warmed through.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the prawn pasta between plates.

To finish, scatter the @grated Italian style hard cheese{1%unit} over the top.